## Common Mistakes

### The Mistake
```javascript
function factorial(n) {
  return n * factorial(n - 1); // Infinite recursion call (stack overflow)!
}
```
*Why this is bad:* Incorrect statement definitions cause unhandled syntax error crashes during execution.

### The Correct Way
```javascript
function factorial(n) {
  if (n <= 1) {
    return 1;
  }
  return n * factorial(n - 1);
}
```
*Why this is good:* Using the validated syntax format ensures program stability.
